@startuml WebSocket Message Flow

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam activityShape rect
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFFFCC

title WebSocket & HTTP Message Processing Flow

|===**Client Side**===

|#EEEBDC| **Client (Python)** |
start
:Connect to ws://host/ws?device_id=xxx;
:WebSocket connected;

|#EEEBDC| **Server Side (FastAPI)** |
:ws_endpoint receives connection;
if (device_id missing?) then (Yes)
    :Close with code 4000;
    stop
else (No)
    :ws_hub.connect(websocket);
    :ws_hub.register_device(connection_id, device_id);
    :device_status_manager.set_idle(device_id);
    :Send {"type": "connected", "accepted": True};
endif

|#EEEBDC| **Client (Python)** |
:Receive connected message;
note right: Ready to send/receive messages

|===**Heartbeat Flow**===

|#EEEBDC| **Client** |
:Send heartbeat;
note right: {"type": "heartbeat", "msg_id": "xxx"}

|#EEEBDC| **Server** |
:receive_text() → handle_ws_message();
if (msg_type == "heartbeat") then (Yes)
    :ws_hub.update_heartbeat(connection_id);
    :device_status_manager.set_idle(device_id);
    :Send heartbeat_ack;
else (No)
    :Ignore/Log unknown type;
endif

|===**Action Command Flow (Server → Client)**===

|#EEEBDC| **Server - Scheduler** |
:scheduler.run_one_cycle(device_id);
:task.execute_reason();
note right: Calls AI model, gets action

|#EEEBDC| **Server - ActionRouter** |
:action_router.send_action() → PendingAction;
:ws_hub.send_to_device(device_id, action_cmd);
note right: {"type": "action_cmd", "msg_id": "xxx", **}

|#EEEBDC| **Server - WebSocketHub** |
:Look up connection_id by device_id;
:websocket.send_json(message);
note right: Connection found?

|#EEEBDC| **Client** |
:Receive action_cmd via WebSocket;
:Execute action on device;
:Send ack via WebSocket;
note right: {"type": "ack", "ref_msg_id": "xxx", "accepted": true}

|#EEEBDC| **Server - ActionRouter** |
:action_router.handle_ack(msg);
note right: Update PendingAction status → ACKNOWLEDGED

|===**Observe Result Flow (Client → Server)**===

|#EEEBDC| **Client** |
:Execute action on device;
:Capture screenshot;
:Send observe_result via HTTP POST;
note right: POST /api/v1/tasks/observe
note right: {"type": "observe_result", "payload": {...}}

|#EEEBDC| **Server - Tasks API** |
:receive_observe_result(message);
note right: Endpoint: POST /observe

|#EEEBDC| **Server - ActionRouter** |
:action_router.handle_observe_result(payload);
note right: Find PendingAction by task_id + step_number
:Update PendingAction.result;
note right: Set future result, notify waiter

|#EEEBDC| **Server - Scheduler** |
:wait_for_result() returns;
:Continue ReAct loop;
note right: Proceed to next step

|===**Disconnect Flow**===

|#EEEBDC| **Client** |
:WebSocket disconnected;

|#EEEBDC| **Server** |
:WebSocketDisconnect exception;
:device_status_manager.set_offline(device_id);
:ws_hub.disconnect(connection_id);
stop

|===**Key Data Structures**===

|#EEEBDC| **PendingAction** |
note top
- action_id: str
- sent_msg_id: str
- task_id: str
- device_id: str
- status: PENDING → ACKNOWLEDGED → COMPLETED
- result: dict
end note

|#EEEBDC| **ActionRouter** |
note top
- _pending_actions: Dict[action_id, PendingAction]
- _pending_actions_by_msg_id: Dict[sent_msg_id, PendingAction]
- _action_futures: Dict[action_id, asyncio.Future]
end note

|#EEEBDC| **WebSocketHub** |
note top
- connections: Dict[connection_id, WebSocket]
- connection_states: Dict[connection_id, ConnectionState]
- _device_connections: Dict[device_id, connection_id]
end note

@enduml
